"No, never," replied Sir Albert;
for though, from the time when it was my fortune to ſave his life in battle he always profeſſed for me the warmeſt friendſhip, yet his own inſenſibility to the ſofter paſſions, deterred me from placing in him the ſame confidence on that ſubject as I readily ſhould on any other. It was by accident that he mentioned to me the arrival of the Father of Conſtance to ſettle ſo near the Caſtle of Dornheim, whither he had before ſo frequently invited me. Had he ever experienced


